      • add

        boolean add(E e)
     throws java.lang.NullPointerException
        Adds a specified element to the binary search tree in an appropriate spot in order to maintain the tree's integrity. Should the specified element be < or = to the root node, the element is placed in the left subtree of the root. Should the specified element be > the root node, the element is placed in the right subtree of the root. If the tree is empty (no root node), the specified element is added as the root node.
        Parameters:
        e - the element to be added to the tree
        Returns:
        true if the specified element to be added is successfully added to the tree
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - If the element specified is null and the tree implementation does not support having null elements.

      • preOrderIterator

        Iterator<E> preOrderIterator()
        Returns an iterator over the elements in the tree, in a depth/height first pre-order traversal sequence. (Visit-Left-Right)
        Returns:
        An iterator over the elements in the tree, in pre-order traversal sequence. The return is not of type java.util.Iterator but instead a custom interface used in CPRG-311.

      • inOrderIterator

        Iterator<E> inOrderIterator()
        Returns an iterator over the elements in the tree, in a depth/height first in-order traversal sequence. (Left-Visit-Right)
        Returns:
        An iterator over the elements in the tree, in in-order traversal sequence. The return is not of type java.util.Iterator but instead a custom interface used in CPRG-311.

      • postOrderIterator
